author: weareinreach
text:
MPox (or monkeypox) is a viral zoonotic disease that has been declared a global health emergency by the W.H.O. - and as of July 2022, has been primarily spreading among gay and bisexual men. Due to the nature of this virus, it is unsafe to assume it will stay that way.

Misinformation can be common as scientists and public health officials learn more about disease outbreaks and varying modes of transmission. Stay informed with reputable sources and learn how to keep yourself safe:

Vaccine Information: https://www.cdc.gov/poxvirus/monkeypox/considerations-for-monkeypox-vaccination.html#vaccine-information

W.H.O. Fact Sheet: https://www.who.int/news-room/fact-sheets/detail/monkeypox

Map of U.S. Cases: https://www.cdc.gov/poxvirus/monkeypox/response/2022/us-map.html

#safehelpisinreach #mpox #lgbtq

author: otimafarmacia
text:
DEFNIÇÃO DE CASO, SEGUNDO O MINISTÉRIO DA SAÚDE:

🟡 Caso suspeito: Indivíduo de qualquer idade que, a partir de 15 de março de 2022, apresente início súbito de erupção cutânea aguda sugestiva de Monkeypox, única ou múltipla, em qualquer parte do corpo (incluindo região genital), associada ou não a adenomegalia ou relato de febre
E
um dos seguintes vínculos:
➡️ Histórico de contato íntimo com desconhecido/a(s) e/ou parceiro/a(s) casual(is), nos últimos 21 dias que antecederam o início dos sinais e sintomas
OU
➡️ Ter vínculo epidemiológico com caso suspeito, provável ou confirmado de Monkeypox, desde 15 de março de 2022, nos 21 dias anteriores ao início dos sinais e sintomas
OU
➡️ Histórico de viagem a país endêmico ou com casos confirmados de Monkeypox nos 21 dias anteriores ao início dos sinais e sintomas
OU
➡️ Ter vínculo epidemiológico com pessoas com histórico de viagem a país endêmico ou país com casos confirmados de Monkeypox, desde 15 de março de 2022, nos 21 dias anteriores ao início dos sinais e sintomas.

🟢 Caso descartado: Indivíduo que atende à definição de caso suspeito com resultado/laudo de exame laboratorial "Negativo/Não Detectável" para Monkeypox vírus (MPXV) por diagnóstico molecular (PCR em Tempo Real e/ou Sequenciamento),
OU
Caso suspeito que durante a investigação clínica, epidemiológica e laboratorial foi diagnosticado outra doença compatível com o quadro apresentado pelo paciente, exceto IST.

🔴 Caso provável: Caso suspeito, submetido a investigação clínica e epidemiológica, E que cursou com quadro clínico compatível com Monkeypox, porém sem possibilidade de confirmação laboratorial por PCR em Tempo Real e/ou sequenciamento.

Para mais informações: https://www.gov.br/saude/pt-br/composicao/svs/resposta-a-emergencias/sala-de-situacao-de-saude/sala-de-situacao-de-monkeypox

#monkeypox #varioladosmacacos #saude #farmácia #otima #farmaciademanipulacao #medicina

author: cqlab.info
text:
REPOST: Supply of the vaccine for the Monkeypox virus (MPV) is very limited at this time, so please follow these steps to determine if you're eligible or not.

As a reminder, MPV is spread through intimate and not casual interactions. If you think you have MPV, @chipublichealth recommends getting tested immediately. Call 773.388.1600 to schedule an MPV screening.

Learn more about the vaccine and other safety recommendations you can take at http://chi.gov/monkeypox.

We're here to break it all down so that you can stay safe and healthy this summer.

#monkeypox #publichealth #safety #chicago

author: ahfrepdom
text:
⚠️ La OMS ha declarado #MONKEYPOX una emergencia sanitaria mundial. Se han reportado más de 17.000 casos de la enfermedad en 75 países. Cualquiera puede contraer el virus y su principal vía de transmisión es a través del contacto cercano con una persona infectada.

❗¿Qué hacer?: evita el contacto estrecho con personas que de quienes desconoces su estatus respecto al virus. Si tienes fiebre y lesiones en la piel, acude al servicio de salud más cercano.

author: danhodapp
text:
Monkeypox vaccine dose #1 complete! Did it hurt? No. Was it simple and easy to get? Also no.
.
Today I drove 30 miles to Santa Clarita and and waited in line for 90 minutes. That’s actually hundreds of miles shorter than some friends from LA traveled to get the vaccine. I was also lucky to have a wait time that was less than half of the ones I’ve been hearing about this week.
.
Anyway, we can do better. And, I dunno, maybe be a good ally and listen to friends who mention they are trying to get the vaccine? It has been stressful to sort through the chaos. Feel free to DM me if you have any questions about the process!

author: hibridamagazine
text:
Com mais de 18 mil casos da #varíoladosmacacos em 78 países, a Organização Mundial da Saúde pediu nesta quarta-feira que os "homens que fazem sexo com homens", 98% de todos os pacientes, diminuam o número de parceiros e de contatos sexuais em uma tentativa de diminuir a transmissão da doença.

Tedros Adhanom, diretor-geral da OMS, também frisou que a #monkeypox não deve ficar restrita a esse grupo e que qualquer pessoa exposta pode se infectar. Ele pediu ainda que os países cuidem da dignidade e dos direitos humanos da comunidade #LGBTQIA: "E estigma e a discriminação podem ser tão perigosos quanto qualquer vírus e alimentar o surto".

Leia a notícia completa no site ou nos stories.

text:

This is disinformation. This narrative is irresponsible and it is dangerous. We have got to do better than that.

Please help us fight against this harmful narrative.

author: maricampagnoli
text:
📍A nota técnica da Anvisa lançada no dia 26/07/2022 trouxe algumas atualizações e orientações que nós controladores já conhecemos bem...

💉Com a grande variedade de cateteres intravenosos disponíveis, existe um risco maior de de complicações, como:  infecção local e sistêmica, flebite, tromboflebite, oclusão, trombose e lesão por pressão (LPP) relacionada a dispositivo para a saúde, entre outros. 

🎯Para evitarmos esses riscos, com base no controle de infecção, temos algumas medidas já conhecidas até por nós. 

🙋🏽‍♀️Mas conta aqui nos comentários, diante de todas essas medidas, qual você acha a mais difícil de implementar no seu trabalho?

📚Referência: Nota técnica Anvisa número 04/2022.

author: stylistmagazine
text:
While doing the daily doomscroll on Twitter, there is one topic that's dominated our timeline above everything else: #monkeypox.⁠
⁠
The disease, which is from the same family of viruses as smallpox, has officially been declared a global health emergency by the World Health Organisation, sparking concerns around the world at the prospect of a new disease to worry about.⁠
⁠
Read more about the virus and how to combat anxiety around it, via the *link in bio*.

“You may have noticed that online people are saying that monkeypox is a gay disease. Please understand that is not true, Anyone can get it. So, while we should make sure the gay community has the support that they need, we also shouldn’t stigmatize them and make it seem like monkeypox is their disease. author: millersvilleu
text:
Throughout 2022, there is a growing concern over the heightened number of #monkeypox virus cases. Dr. Eric Ryndock, a professor of biology at Millersville University, wants to keep the community updated and informed about the virus. He says that the virus is genetically related to the one that causes smallpox. Monkeypox was discovered in 1958 and, despite its name, is not usually found in monkeys.

Ryndock explains that monkeypox is usually classified as a zoonotic infection, meaning that the virus is transmitted from animals to people. This type of transmission occurs when people are bitten or scratched by infected animals or encounter their bodily fluids. Prior to this year, incidents of monkeypox were generally limited to central and western Africa. Countries outside of this normal reporting range, including the U.S., have begun reporting monkeypox cases in 2022.

Ryndock says, “This led to the suspicion that person-person transmission was occurring, which is expected to be linked to direct contact with infectious sores and bodily fluids. If monkeypox transmits through respiratory droplets, similar to SARS-CoV-2, it’s expected to be a rare event and would only occur if an individual has sores in their throat.” Want the rest of our story? Click on the link in our bio.

author: haruntulunay
text:
I am happy in the advocacy work I have been doing for #HIV and #monkeypox . I know that someone, somewhere feels empowered and supported by listening or watching my story. They feel what is in my heart and why I am trying to be an advocate for all others who can’t speak up.

If I tell you about my past, it’s never because I want you to feel sorry for me, but so you can understand why I am who I am. Haters don’t really hate you in the end. In fact, they hate themselves because you are a reflection of what they wish to be.

Before you judge me, make sure you are perfect. If you are not, then shut up.

author: pubhealthdork
text:
So sorry to have to keep sharing troubling news. As I’ve been saying, Monkeypox (MPV) is serious! The last time the World Health Organization (W.H.O) declared a global health emergency was for COVID-19! A WHO declaration of a global public health emergency does not mean this is a pandemic yet. We will see where we are in the coming weeks.

It is NOT a STI/STD! While trans and gay communities have been hit hard, it is not just impacting the trans and gay community!

Testing is lagging in the United States so we do not have a complete picture of what is taking place here yet.

This is the first headline announcement I’ve seen that wasn’t giving anti-Black or anti-LGBTQ+ sentiments.

Please review the fact checked info on my page about it. There have been more 16,000 cases globally, and the virus has reached 75 countries and territories.

Image Text:
NPR Breaking News: W.H.O declares monkeypox spread a global health emergency

“I have decided that the global #Monkeypox outbreak is of international concern.” - WHO Director-General Tedros Adhanom
Ghebreyesus

#globalhealth #monkeypox #mpv #outbreak

author: mafeinfectologista
text:
MONKEYPOX: OMS declara que surto da doença constitui uma emergência de saúde pública. 🐵

Nesse momento, você já deve ter ouvido falar de Monkeypox (ou "Varíola Símia"). Esse novo vírus circulante está nas manchetes desde o início de 2022, trazendo de volta a discussão sobre a Varíola (Smallpox), uma doença 'prima' que foi declarada como erradicada em 1980 pela OMS, após três anos do último caso, graças à vacinação global.

Atualmente, em 23 de julho de 2022, temos 16.836 casos reportados em 74 países diferentes, incluindo o Brasil, com 592 casos confirmados (dados do CDC)

Os sintomas da varíola dos macacos podem incluir:
- febre 🌡
- dor de cabeça
- dor no corpo
- linfonodo aumentados (pequenos caroços dentro da pele)
- calafrios
- lesões de pele que se assemelham a espinhas ou bolhas, aparecendo no rosto, boca e em outras partes do corpo, como mãos, pés, tronco, e - principalmente durante o surto de 2022 - em genitais ou ânus.

Como pode ser transmitida? por contato íntimo direto com as lesões, crostas ou fluidos corporais; exposição a secreções respiratórias durante contato prolongado, ou durante contato físico íntimo, como beijo ou sexo.

🚨 O momento atual mostra uma concentração de casos entre homens que fazem sexo com homens (HSH), porém é importante lembrar que a doença não afeta somente essa parcela da população e esse cluster de acometimento não deve levar à estigmas ligados à sexualidade e gênero das pessoas.

Caso você apresente esses sintomas, procure atendimento médico. O Ministério da Saúde preparou um fluxo para atendimento, diagnóstico e acompanhamento dos pacientes.

Confira na íntegra: https://www.paho.org/pt/noticias/23-7-2022-diretor-geral-da-oms-declara-que-surto-monkeypox-constitui-uma-emergencia-saude

#infectologia #monkeypox #varioladosmacacos

author: khou11
text:
The Houston Health Department is allowing those with a high risk of monkeypox to get the vaccine, which includes those on HIV pre-exposure prophylaxis, also known as PrEP.

The vaccine is being offered to two different groups of people, but they are prioritizing the first group which includes those who have had contact with someone who has monkeypox and people who went to a venue where there was a high exposure to the virus through skin and sexual contact.

The second group includes those who are at high risk of getting the virus.

Click the link in our bio to read more.
#khou #khou11 #monkeypox #houstonhealth

author: enb__ee
text:
It’s almost as if scientists haven’t been warning about this possibility since smallpox vaccinations stopped being standard about forty years ago. Like they haven’t seen a significant rise in cases of MPX in unvaccinated populations since 2005.

You would think COVID has taught us that a health problem across the globe, is soon a health problem ACROSS the globe. But no, eurocentric governments and leaders are going to continue as normal while people in non-eurocentric countries suffer…. Until it impacts their country of course… and then they’re going to find a scapegoat and downplay the potential impact to the rest of their population.

Gotta make sure the money circulates back into their own, or their friends pockets.

I’m so tired.

MPX is not an STI. If You haven’t been vaccinated for small pox you are way more likely to contract it if you come into close contact with someone that has it, or touched something an infected person has touched or are breathing in their respiratory particles. You can contract it by sitting on a couch hours after someone with MPX sat on it. If you’re not vaccinated you are at risk of contracting it and spreading it regardless of your (or others) sex, gender, sexuality, or age.

Wear masks. Even gloves.

Let your local leaders know the facts. Let them know that vaccines need to be made widely available. And tell them they need to act fast. If they don’t want another lockdown they better stop playing “pretend everything is normal” and be proactive.

We haven’t stopped being in a pandemic since 2020.

Image description: text reads “Weird, how a disease that dates back to 1958 & has since indiscriminately impacted thousands of unvaccinated people, has suddenly been repackaged as an STI for gay people. It couldn’t possibly be connected with how another pandemic might impact the economy again… or the fact that the overturning of Roe vs. Wade has put a lot of pro LGBTQ+ rulings on the chopping block… right?”

#mpx #monkeypox #vaccine #smallpox

author: robertajungmann
text:
A Organização Mundial da Saúde (OMS) admitiu nesta quarta-feira (27), que a varíola do macaco, também chamada de monkeypox, pode ser transmitida sexualmente.

O conselheiro da organização, Andy Seale, declarou: "Em resumo, eles [especialistas] concluíram que essa é claramente uma doença transmitida durante o sexo e, portanto, é configurada como uma doença sexualmente transmissível".

A OMS recomenda a diminuição de parceiros sexuais e reconsiderar ter novos parceiros sexuais como formas de prevenção.

Saiba mais clicando no link da bio!

📸: Divulgação
.
.
.
.

author: blogedenevaldoalves
text:
O Brasil tem 813 casos confirmados da varíola dos macacos (monkeypox), segundo dados do Ministério da Saúde. A líder técnica da Organização Mundial da Saúde (OMS) para a doença, Rosamund Lewis, disse que a situação no país “é muito preocupante” e que os casos podem estar subnotificados por não haver testes suficientes à disposição.

“É importante que as autoridades também tomem conhecimento da emergência de saúde pública e de interesse internacional, das recomendações e tomem as medidas adequadas”, declarou. Ela também disse que o surto pode ser interrompido com “estratégias certas nos grupos certos”. “Mas o tempo está passando e todos precisamos nos unir para que isso aconteça”, acrescentou.

No sábado (23), o diretor-geral da OMS, Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus, anunciou que a varíola dos macacos configura emergência de saúde pública de interesse internacional. “Temos um surto que se espalhou rapidamente pelo mundo, através de novas formas de transmissão, sobre as quais entendemos muito pouco, e que se encaixa nos critérios do Regulamento Sanitário Internacional”, declarou.

O Ministério da Saúde destacou, por meio de nota, que a doença é prioridade para a pasta, que faz constante monitoramento e analisa a todo momento a situação epidemiológica para definir orientações e ações de vigilância e resposta à doença no país. “Todas as medidas hoje anunciadas pela Organização Mundial da Saúde (OMS) já são realizadas pelo Brasil desde o início de julho de forma a realizar uma vigilância oportuna da doença”, diz o texto. (Diário PE)

author: all_about_microbiology_
text:
The rapidly spreading monkeypox outbreak constitutes a global health emergency, WHO director-general Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus declared recently.
Amid a surge in cases, World Health Organization (WHO) Technical Lead has said that the rapidly spreading monkeypox outbreak can be stopped.
Speaking to reporters, Rosamund Lewis said, "We do at this moment still believe that this outbreak of monkeypox can be stopped with the right strategies in the right groups but time is going by and we all need to pull together to make that happen."
Monkeypox outbreak constitutes a global health emergency, WHO director-general Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus declared on Saturday.

The WHO label - a "public health emergency of international concern" - is designed to trigger a coordinated international response and could unlock funding to collaborate on sharing vaccines and treatments.

First identified in monkeys, the virus is transmitted chiefly through close contact with an infected person. Until 2022, the viral disease has rarely spread outside Africa where it is endemic.

"WHO is still working towards determining a global coordination mechanism. At the moment, it's something that's still in discussion," the WHO official added.
.
.

author: noams_ark
text:
***משרד הבריאות פרסם מחדש את ההתוויות לחיסון אבעבועות הקוף, בצורה ברורה בהרבה***

ההתוויות לחיסון נגד אבעבועות הקוף, לפני חשיפה לנגיף (כטיפול מונע):
גברים, כולל א.נשים על הקשת הטרנסית, בני 18 לפחות, שנולדו החל משנת 1980 ומקבלים PrEP למניעת הדבקה ב-HIV
או
גברים, כולל א.נשים על הקשת הטרנסית, בני 18 לפחות שנולדו החל משנת 1980, חיוביים ל-HIV *וגם* אובחנו מאז ינואר 2022 עם עגבת פעילה, כלמידיה או זיבה.

אנשים שנולדו לפני 1980 חוסנו לאבעבועות שחורות בעבר ואולי עוד מוגנים (לפחות חלקית) מאבעבועות הקוף. מאחר שכמות החיסונים מוגבלת מאוד ,כרגע הם לא בהתוויה לחיסון.

סיכום הדברים שעודכנו:
הבהרות שהחיסון ינתן גם לטרנס*, שמי שכבר חלה באבעבועות הקוף לא יחוסן, ושנוטלי PrEP אלה רק אנשים שהשתמשו בתרופה לפחות פעם אחת בין 01/01/2022 ל-30/06/2022 (כולל)

#monkeypox #vaccine #אבעבועות_הקוף #חיסון

author: impulserio
text:
Em 22 de julho de 2022, havia 16.836 casos relatados de Monkey Pox em 74 locais em todo o mundo. Estima-se que isso seja muito menor do que a contagem real de casos.

Agora que a OMS declarou a varíola dos macacos ou varíola dos macacos uma emergência de saúde internacional, há muitas dúvidas, aqui apresentamos mais informações sobre o assunto, lembre-se que esses dados continuam em desenvolvimento, por isso é recomendável estar sempre conectado.

Devemos agir agora, entender os sintomas e nos cuidar.
Juntos, podemos evitar uma disseminação significativa, mas cada um de nós deve fazer sua parte

author: drberrypierre
text:
In this episode of Real Physician Reacts we will be revisiting a conversation we had on our Medicine Monday series where we introduced the Lunch and Learn Community to the topic of the monkeypox virus. At the time it was more of an informational session as we had just a few cases to even discuss at the time but clearly didn’t know where we were headed.

At the time of the episode, we are currently at 2400+ cases of monkeypox just here in the United States and it does seem to not be slowing down anytime soon. After a spirited discussion on my TikTok platform, I figured it was best we revisit the discussion and try to answer a question I am getting more and more lately.

Are we prepared for a monkeypox outbreak?

author: thenakedtruthcrew
text:
There have been more than 18,000 cases monkeypox reported globally from 78 countries, with the majority in Europe, the World Health Organization said. The WHO declared the outbreak a global health emergency on Saturday.

Indian Council of Medical Research (ICMR) said it has isolated the monkeypox virus and is inviting vaccine makers to consider making shots after the country reported some cases of infection.

India reported its first confirmed case of monkeypox earlier this month. The vaccine candidate and the diagnostic kit can be developed under the Public-Private Partnership and the last date submission of the "Expressions of Interest" will be August 10, the ICMR said.

So far, four cases of Monkeypox have surfaced in India -- three from Kerala and one from Delhi.

Monkeypox is a viral disease that causes flu-like symptoms and skin lesions

author: svatranathemasklab
text:
On July 23, the World Health Organization (WHO) declared monkeypox a global public health emergency of international concern.

Here's what you should know to stay safe!

Globally, over 16,000 cases of monkeypox have been reported from 75 countries and there have been five deaths so far due to the outbreak. In the WHO South-East Asia region, besides India, one case has been noticed in Thailand.

India witnessed the fourth case of monkeypox after a man from Delhi with no history of international travel tested positive and was admitted to Lok Nayak Jai Prakash (LNJP) Hospital. The first three cases in India were reported from Kerala.

Delhi Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal tweeted, "Our best team is on the case to prevent the spread and protect Delhiites."

Monkeypox virus is transmitted from infected animals to humans via indirect or direct contact. Human-to-human transmission can occur through direct contact with infectious skin or lesions, including face-to-face, skin-to-skin, and respiratory droplets.

“The protocol for treating monkeypox is the same as COVID-19 and people who have travel history are more vulnerable. To protect yourself from monkeypox, wear masks and observe social distancing. In case of any suspicious symptoms, report to the doctor immediately,” advised Dr Suresh Kumar, Medical Director of Lok Nayak Jai Prakash (LNJP) Hospital in conversation with News18.

The Mask Lab's medical-grade 3 Ply surgical masks and FFP2 (N95 grade) respirators will help protect you from harmful airborne particles, i.e., smog, smoke, dust, pollution, germs, bacteria, and viruses, with >99% filtration efficiency.

author: audrybabe
text:
from @dorcasadedoja As always, it's never about panic. It's about making sure folks are informed. Everything Monkeypox I could find because the health communication just hasnt been good enough so far.

Tecovirimat is also known as TPOXX.

You do not have to have sex to test positive for Monkeypox.

Monkeypox cases have doubled and tripled in areas around the country within the past few weeks. We need to collectively move with more caution.

Monkeypox is related to the smallpox virus, so smallpox vaccines are being used to contain this Monkeypox outbreak.

Captions are in "alt text" due to app constraints.

Now isn't the time for sharing or posting information that hasn't been fact checked. Please do not share graphics because they look cute. A lot of things lve seen floating around are beautifully incorrect.

Other public health/medical folks please feel free to jump in. I fact checked a million times, but I'm still human.

author: intimudaindonesia
text:
Terjemahan:

“Pria gay terkena dampak dari virus Monkeypox" tidak sama dengan "hanya pria gay yang bisa terkena virus Monkeypox" atau "orang terinfeksi virus Monkeypox karena mereka gay".

Plus, kita juga perlu menginformasikan kepada publik tentang apa yang tidak mentransmisikan virus Monkeypox.”

Jangan sampai membuat kesalahan yang sama seperti dengan HIV.

———

@siputriwidi melalui akun Twitternya membahas terkait bagaimana kelompok gay terdampak dari transmisi virus Monkeypox yang mana hal ini bukanlah alasan untuk melakukan diskriminasi terhadap kelompok rentan khususnya gay atau LSL pada kasus ini.

Hal tersebut juga bukan berarti “hanya kelompok tertentu (LSL) yang dapat terinfeksi virus Monkeypox,” dan “orang terinfeksi virus Monkeypox karena orientasi seksualnya.”

Hal ini memiliki pola yang sama dalam stigma dan diskriminasi terhadap kelompok populasi kunci dalam transmisi HIV. Beberapa kelompok memang terkena dampak dari HIV, namun bukan berarti hal ini dapat menjadi alasan untuk melakukan stigma dan diskriminasi. Karena setiap orang rentan akan transmisi HIV dan stigma serta diskriminasi tidak akan menurunkan angka infeksi baru.

#virusmonkeypox
#monkeypoxindonesia
#diskriminasi

author: briandouglasjames
text:
Let’s talk about 𝗦𝗧𝗜𝗚𝗠𝗔:⁣
⁣
-“a mark of disgrace associated with a particular circumstance, quality, or person.”⁣
⁣
How dare people shame others when they don’t even understand what the hell they are talking about. I am so over people touting “bless your heart” or “no shade” or even worse just being downright assholes to other people. ⁣
⁣
I had THREE people in my DM’s today telling me that the information I am sharing about monkey pox is fake news and that it’s god’s way of punishing the gays! ⁣
⁣
What they actual F**K!?!?⁣
⁣
A few days ago I went down some comment rabbit holes on accounts I follow and I legit started crying because people are just so obnoxiously rude and distasteful to other humans. ⁣
⁣
I will never say the words “let’s agree to disagree” when it comes to my humans rights as a gay man. So don’t ever come at me with that. ⁣
⁣
I was born in 1989 so I don’t have the same history and experience of the AIDS pandemic as many of my community and friends. I do however love to learn and have so much empathy for people. I won’t go too far down this route tonight but do your research and learn about the Literal Hell they went through and the STIGMA that is still there.⁣
⁣
MONKEYPOX is ravaging through the gay community but it is not an STI. It is spread by skin to skin contact, intimate face to face like kissing/cuddling, and there is a bunch they are still finding out. It is not a GAY DISEASE so STOP! ⁣
⁣
I do think some of the messaging is needed because the LGBTQAI+ community does need to be on alert but the messaging also needs to make sure people don’t think this is “nothing” or “just the gays”…⁣
⁣
The response has been terrible mostly. People can’t get tested, can’t get treatment, and the vaccine rollout is finally getting better. This is not funny and this is not something to shame people about especially when you don’t even understand a single damn thing about it. ⁣
⁣
We have friends that are going through some of the worst pain from this disease and then the biggest shame spirals because of others! ⁣
⁣
Please, just treat people with compassion and with the same decency you want to be treated with. ⁣

author: k24tamankotabangka
text:
WHO menetapkan Monkeypox atau cacar monyet sebagai darurat kesehatan global. Apakah kondisi ini berpotensi menjadi pandemi??

Cek infonya lebih lanjut ya Sobat Sehat!

Meskipun cacar monyet belum ditemukan di Indonesia, sebaiknya jaga selalu protokol kesehatan! Terutama jaga kebersihan tangan Anda.

Bawa selalu hand sanitizer kemanapun dan dimanapun Anda berada. Tersedia berbagai produk hand sanitizer di Apotek K-24 & K24Klik. Lengkap 24 jam!

author: momsindonesia
text:
Moms, udah denger berita terbaru, belum? Soal penyakit Monkeypox atau Cacar Monyet, yang dikabarkan oleh Organisasi Kesehatan Dunia (WHO) sebagai darurat kesehatan dan menjadi perhatian internasional.⁣
⁣
Meskipun sampai saat ini kasus Cacar Monyet belum ada di Indonesia, tapi, gak ada salahnya kok tetap waspada dan selalu jaga kesehatan Moms, si Kecil atau anggota keluarga lainnya, dengan hidup bersih dan sehat.

author: therealsilversteele
text:
Day 16 of MonkeyPox symptoms. 🐒🦠 I stepped outside to take the dog out and decided to take a progress pic of how my lesions are looking today. The goop you see on them is Vaseline. I’m very scared of potential facial scarring… I’m not picking at anything and just letting it run it’s course naturally.
If I scar, I scar, and my skin will just tell the story of my journey.. but I hope not. Today I shared my story with @abc13houston and @npr on their @houstonpubmedia show Town Square. I’ve been featured on @kprc2 @univision and @telemundo in Houston, but I want to give a special shoutout to @khou11 @janellekhou for doing the most beautiful coverage of my story.
As a result of my story and others’ snapping the population to attention, today Houston has been vaccinating high risk people all day… I’ve had friends telling me they overheard people saying “I’m here because I saw that guy on TV and I don’t want that to be me”, and that’s music to my ears. Thank you all for your support, your kindness, and for giving this matter the attention and vigilance it commands. Stay safe and I love you all!
#monkeypox #houston #houstonproud #virus #nostigma #yallmeansall #gay #vaccine

author: imakahi_ugm
text:
[PRESS RELEASE KAJIAN RUTIN 5: MONKEYPOX atau CACAR MONYET]

Monkeypox adalah penyakit akibat virus yang ditularkan melalui binatang. Kasus Monkeypox ini pertama kali ditemukan pada tahun 1958 di Denmark. Pada tahun 2022 WHO telah mencatat lebih dari 140 kasus Monkeypox terjadi di beberapa negara, sehingga menjadi masalah kesehatan yang mendapat perhatian dunia ditengah Covid-19 dan virus hepatitis akut.

Pada kajian rutin kelima yang telah dilaksanakan pada Senin, 11 Juli 2022 telah dikaji mengenai penyebab dan cara penularan Monkeypox.

Berikut adalah press release yang bisa dibaca bersama. Selamat membaca!!!

Departemen Kajian Stratagis
-------------
#BerpaduSepadan
#Vivaveteriner

author: dradeltaderma
text:
El virus de la viruela símica o monkeypox puede transmitirse mediante gotas o contacto con las lesiones cutáneas o fluidos de las personas o animales infectados. 🦠

La mayoría de los casos se han presentado en hombres jóvenes que mantienen relaciones sexuales con otros hombres.

Periodo de incubación de 5-21 días. 🗓

El tratamiento es sintomático, pero es importante realizar un diagnóstico temprano para evitar complicaciones y propagación del virus. #dermatologia #dermatologa #monkeypox #virueladelmono #viruelasimica #lavadodemanos

Deep thanks to AD @iguessnick and get vaccinated everyone <3

author: pontualportal
text:
A Opas (Organização Pan-Americana da Saúde) afirmou nesta quarta-feira (27) que as negociações para compra de doses de vacinas contra monkeypox (varíola dos macacos) para países do continente americano estão avançadas, mas as doses devem ser limitadas neste ano.

"Nós temos esperanças de que vamos ter vacinas neste ano [...] limitadas, porque temos somente um produtor e será pouco a pouco", afirmou Marcos Espinal, subdiretor interino da Opas.

Marcelo Queiroga, ministro da Saúde, afirmou nesta segunda (25) que não há previsão de vacinar toda a população contra a varíola dos macacos e que a prioridade deve ser o isolamento dos casos confirmados e orientações sobre as formas de contágio.

📌 Saiba de tudo pelo link na bio.

#portalpontual #opas #vacina #monkeypox #varioladosmacacos #doença #marceloqueiroga

text:
REPOST: Supply of the vaccine for the Monkeypox virus (MPV) is very limited at this time, so please visit our linkin.bio for an updated list of where appts. and walk-ins are available to eligible seekers.

As a reminder, MPV is spread through intimate and not casual interactions. If you think you have MPV, @chipublichealth recommends getting tested immediately. Call 773.388.1600 to schedule an MPV screening.

Learn more about the vaccine and other safety recommendations you can take at http://chi.gov/monkeypox.

We're here to break it all down so that you can stay safe and healthy this summer.

text:
Atlanta – The Georgia Department of Public Health (DPH) has begun receiving limited doses of monkeypox vaccine. To date, Georgia has received approximately 3,000 doses of JYNNEOS vaccine – enough for 1,500 individuals since this is a two-dose vaccine series. The vaccine has been distributed upon request to health departments and for vaccination events in two counties. Allocations of monkeypox vaccine from the federal government will increase as production of the vaccine ramps up. 
To date, DPH has confirmed 93 monkeypox cases in Georgia, all among men living in metro Atlanta.

The majority of these cases identify as men who have sex with men

Is this part of the agenda to de-popularize men?????

author: helvetas.peru
text:
🙌✅ ¡La información es importante! La #ViruelaDelMono (#monkeypox) se transmite a través del contacto directo con lesiones en la #piel, fluidos corporales, salpicadura involuntaria de #saliva en los ojos o boca al toser, hablar o estornudar y mediante objetos contaminados por el #virus como ropa de cama y vendajes sucios.😷🦠

🟠Síntomas (Fase de invasión):
▪️Fiebre
▪️Dolor de cabeza
▪️Dolor muscular
▪️Inflamación de los ganglios linfáticos
▪️Cansancio intenso

🔴Síntomas (Fase de erupción):
▪️Erupciones cutáneas en distintas partes del cuerpo que pueden causar mucha picazón y dolor.

⚠️Si presentas algunos de los síntomas descritos y crees que podría tratarse de esta infección, llama a la Línea 113, opción 6, o acude al establecimiento de salud más cercano para recibir atención por sospecha de viruela del mono.

🌐Para más información ingresa aquí: http://www.gob.pe/virueladelmono

author: nychealthy
text:
Monkeypox is spreading in NYC, but there are things you can do to prevent it.
.
Monkeypox is most often spread through direct contact with a rash or sores of someone who has the virus.
.
To lower your chance of getting monkeypox, consider how much skin-to-skin contact will occur at the event you plan to attend.
.
Lower risk activities include festivals, events and concerts where attendees are fully clothed and unlkely to share skin-to-skin contact.
.
.
.
#monkeypox #monkeypoxvaccine #monkeypoxnyc #monkeypoxvirus #monkeypoxnyc #publichealth

author: tvcenariooficial
text:
Varíola dos macacos: OMS aconselha a, no momento, que homens que fazem sexo com homens reduzam o número de parceiros

O diretor da Organização Mundial da Saúde (OMS) aconselhou, nesta quarta-feira (27), que homens que fazem sexo com homens, reduzam, neste momento, o número de parceiros sexuais, a fim de diminuir o risco de exposição à varíola dos macacos (monkeypox).

Além disso, Tedros Adhanom Ghebreysus reforçou que "estigma e discriminação podem ser tão perigosos quanto qualquer vírus e podem alimentar o surto".

Tedros pediu que comunidades e indivíduos se informassem e levassem os riscos da doença a sério, além de tomarem as medidas necessárias para interromper a transmissão e proteger grupos vulneráveis.

"A melhor maneira de fazer isso é reduzir o risco de exposição. Isso significa fazer escolhas seguras para você e para os outros. Para homens que fazem sexo com homens, isso inclui, no momento, reduzir o número de parceiros sexuais, reconsiderar o sexo com novos parceiros e trocar detalhes de contato com novos parceiros para permitir o acompanhamento, se necessário", disse Tedros.

Confira a matéria completa no site da TV Cenário: https://tvcenario.com/blog/2022/07/27/variola-dos-macacos-oms-aconselha-a-no-momento-que-homens-que-fazem-sexo-com-homens-reduzam-o-numero-de-parceiros/

text:

⠀
O encontro é aberto a profissionais de enfermagem das Comissões de Controle de Infecção Hospitalar (CCIHs) de instituições filiadas. Os interessados em participar devem confirmar presença pelo e-mail secretaria@sindhoesg.org.br até o dia 10 de agosto.⠀
⠀
Criado em 2010 e coordenado pela enfermeira Luciene Paiva Potenciano, o Grupo de Estudos da NR-32 do Sindhoesg reúne-se regularmente para o debate de temas relacionados à segurança e à saúde dos pacientes e dos profissionais de saúde.⠀

author: rajeev_maharaj
text:
Monkeypox cases in the world continue to rise.

Over 7 000 of the total cases were identified in just the last 10 days.

A quick reminder that WHO's declaration today of Monkeypox as a Public Health Emergency of International Concern (PHEIC) does NOT mean that it is now a Pandemic.

A PHEIC can quickly become a pandemic, as in the case of COVID-19. Monkeypox now joins COVID-19 (2020) and Polio (2014) as the ongoing PHEIC's declared by WHO.

It is important to know why Monkeypox was declared as a PHEIC:

The Monkeypox virus is endemic to Central and Western Africa, ever since the first human case in 1970. However, it has now spread to at least 80 non-endemic countries in just 3 months.

The human Monkeypox virus (hMPXv) has also behaved differently in comparison to previous outbreaks. It has picked up several mutations along the way, and its closest ancestor virus is related to the virus from the Nigerian outbreak during 2017. Furthermore, the presentation of symptoms in infected individuals also differs greatly from previous outbreaks.

Majority of the cases have been detected in the GBMSM community (Gay, Bisexual, Men who have Sex with Men), and has spread in sexual networks, with transmission occurring likely during sexual intercourse and/or close contact during sexual encounters. This is different to the known modes of transmission and further studies are required to understand this.

author: ldnlgbtqcentre
text:
The World Health Organisation has declared Monkeypox as a national health emergency.

Londoners who meet the criteria are able to book a vaccine at Guys and St Thomas' hospital. To do this, follow the steps below:

➡️Click the link in our bio
➡️Tap on the Monkeypox booking square
➡️It'll open your email provider with a pre-populated email
➡️Fill out the details that are requested
➡️Send email

You can also contact your local sexual health clinic and see if they are offering the vaccine.

🏳️‍🌈 Guy’s and St Thomas’ Hospital (London Bridge) is holding walk-in clinics over the next two weekends. You don’t have to live in London to go. Timings: 11.30am to 6pm on July 30-31, and from 9.30am to 5.30pm on August 6-7. Wait time expected to be long. Some waited around 3 hours last time, so take water, snacks and SPF!

You can also call them to book an appointment on 020 71884040

🏳️‍🌈 John Hunter Clinic (Chelsea and Westminster) – appointments on upcoming Wednesdays – Call 020 3315 4040 – be persistent and patient.

🏳️‍🌈 Clifden Centre (Homerton) – call 020 7683 4103 – be persistent and patient.

🏳️‍🌈 Mortimer Market Centre (Warren Street) is adding vaccine apts to its online booking site. You can find this URL in our Monkeypox highlight. Check back regularly.

🏳️‍🌈 10 Hammersmith Broadway (Hammersmith) – call 020 3315 1010 – be persistent and patient.

🏳️‍🌈 Barking sexual health clinic – call 0208 970 5724 and press option 1 then 1 again.

🏳️‍🌈 Falcon Road SHSWL (Clapham Junction) has been offering Monkeypox vaccines to some MSM attending check-ups there.

We’ll update this caption as and when new information comes in!

Stay safe you gorgeous lot 💙

#monkeypox #monkeypoxinformation #monkeypoxvaccine #monkeypoxlondon #sexualhealthlondon

author: drharbiinfectologista
text:
🩺A Monkeypox (erroneamente chamada de Varíola dos macacos) é uma doença causada por um vírus, cujo reservatorio natural nao são os macacos e sim pequenos roedores(p ex. esquilos).

➡️A Monkeypox pode ser transmitida de pessoa para pessoa, através do contato pessoal próximo e prolongado com lesões de pele e suas secreções, objetos recentemente contaminados ou com secreções respiratórias.

⚠️A doença costuma causar alguns sintomas como:
👉Febre;
👉Dor muscular;
👉Dor de cabeça;
👉Aumento de gânglios (linfonodos);
👉Cansaço (fadiga) e
👉Lesões de pele

As lesões de pele podem ser vesículas, pápulas, pústulas ou crostas, que podem aparecer em todo o corpo, inclusive na região genital.

Como me proteger?🤔

➡️Você pode reduzir o risco de se infectar limitando o contato próximo com pessoas que estão com a doença ou casos suspeitos, além de manter medidas simples como a lavagem regular das mãos e o uso de máscaras(se for se aproximar de algum casos suspeito/confirmado).

Ao apresentar sintomas, entre em isolamento e faça contato com seu médico de confiança!😉
.
.
.
#drharbiothman #infectologista #infectologia #varioladosmacacos #monkeypox #doençainfecciosa #parauapebas #maraba

author: portaltabloideob
text:
A Secretaria de Estado de Saúde de Minas Gerais (SES-MG) atualizou nessa terça-feira (26) os dados referentes à monkeypox, conhecida como varíola dos macacos. De acordo com a pasta, o número de casos confirmados segue em 44 no Estado. Outros 69 pacientes suspeitos, de 23 municípios distintos, são investigados pela secretaria.

Até o momento, 70 casos foram descartados e outros dois foram classificados como prováveis para a doença. Conforme a Secretaria de Estado de Saúde, todos os casos confirmados até o momento no Estado são do sexo masculino, com idades entre 22 e 48 anos, e em boas condições clínicas.

Ao todo, duas pessoas estão internadas em Minas Gerais, devido à necessidade clínica e isolamento. Os indivíduos que tiveram contato com os contaminados pela doença estão em monitoramento.

>>> Leia a matéria completa em nosso site. Link na bio e no story. <<<

#saúde #varíoladosmacacos #monkeypox #minasgerais #portaltabloideob

author: taboaoeregiao
text:
TABOÃO, EMBU E ITAPECERICA - Varíola do macacos passa a ter status de emergência de saúde internacional

Não bastasse a continuidade da pandemia de coronavirus e uma guera internacional, a varíola dos macacos (ou com o nome gringo monkeypox) foi declarada como emergência de saúde internacional. São mais de 16 mil casos notificados em 75 países, podendo ser muito mais. O surto, segundo o Comitê de Emergência para monkeypox, é moderado a nível global.

Mas, calma, a situação não exige desespero e sim atenção. Temos um quadro de cerca de 500 pessoas infectadas no estado de São Paulo e apenas duas na cidade de Taboão da Serra, três em Embu das Artes e Itapecerica da Serra.

A varíola dos macacos é mais branda do que a varíola humana (smallpox) e causa bem menos danos do que a antiga doença. Dificilmente deve levar o infectado à morte.

Os primeiros sintomas são parecidos com uma gripe (febre, dor de cabeça e no corpo), mais tarde aparecem algumas lesões na pele e são elas que transmitem o vírus da varíola dos macacos. A infecção normalmente se dá com o contato físico direto com essas lesões na pele, exposições diretas a secreções respiratórias, contato sexual ou com materiais contaminados (com roupas, toalhas e talheres).

Segundo o Instituto Butantan: "A OMS descreve quadros diferentes de sintomas para casos suspeitos, prováveis e confirmados. Passa a ser considerado um caso suspeito qualquer pessoa, de qualquer idade, que apresente erupções na pele de forma aguda e inexplicável e esteja em um país onde a varíola causada pelo monkeypox não é endêmica. Se este quadro for acompanhado de um ou mais dos demais sintomas (febre, fadiga, linfoadenopatia (inchaço dos linfonodos), dores musculares), é necessário fazer exame de reação em cadeia da polimerase (PCR) para confirmar ou descartar a doença."

#taboãodaserra #taboão #embu #embudasartes #itapecerica #itapecericadaserra #saude #monkeypox #varioladosmacacos #variola #macacos

author: antonyalexbagalue_phd
text:
Monkeypox is on the rise. Here's what you should know:

1) Anyone can get monkeypox.

2) Monkeypox spreads by close physical contact with an infectious rash, touching items such as clothing or bed sheets used by someone who has the virus, or through respiratory droplets. A pregnant woman can also spread the virus to her fetus through the placenta.

3) Monkeypox symptoms can include fever, headache, swollen lymph nodes, chills, exhaustion, muscle and backaches, and a rash. Sometimes a rash is the only sign of monkeypox. The rash can look like pimples or blisters and go through different stages over 2-4 weeks. These sores often appear on the face, palms, soles of the feet, chest, or genitals.

4) Antiviral drugs and vaccines intended to treat smallpox can also be used to prevent and treat monkeypox.

5) Individuals who are immunosuppressed and more likely to get severely ill from monkeypox can discuss with their doctor the possibility of taking antivirals such as tecovirimat (TPOXX) for further protection.

#monkeypox #monkeypoxsymptoms #employeehealth #employeebenefits #expertmedicalopinion

author: mctx_publichealth
text:
Monkeypox Update – July 27, 2022

DSHS and local health departments are investigating cases of monkeypox that are part of an international outbreak. The disease, which can cause a serious skin rash, appears to be spreading largely via direct contact with the skin or saliva of an infected person. Most cases so far have been among men who have sex with men, so that population should be especially aware of the situation and take precautions to avoid direct contact with anyone with a rash. Anyone who develops a rash should avoid direct contact with other people and contact their health care provider as soon as possible for next steps.

DSHS has received a shipment of 14,780 doses of the JYNNEOS monkeypox vaccine. DSHS immediately forwarded 5,120 doses to Dallas County Health and Human Services. The remainder of the state doses will be provided to local health departments and DSHS regional offices to vaccinate people with a documented or presumed exposure to the monkeypox virus. The shipment represents all the JYNNEOS vaccine available now to Texas from the federal Strategic National Stockpile. Houston and Harris County have received a separate shipment of approximately 5,000 doses from the SNS.

For up-to-date case counts for monkeypox in Texas, please see: https://dshs.texas.gov/news/updates.shtm#monkeypox.

#monkeypox #publichealth

author: dr.amylouise
text:
MONKEYPOX: what do I need to know?

Monkeypox is caused by a virus that is part of the poxviruses family which causes zoonotic disease (from animals) that can ‘jump’ to humans. This virus family is also responsible for smallpox (eradicated by vaccination), molluscum contagiosum, + others.

Monkeypox is spread by any direct contact (not only sexual) with someone who has it, + anyone can get it.

Why worry?
“Rash” and “flu-like symptoms” don’t sound so bad. However, the monkeypox rash is often painful. Lesions are firm or rubbery, round, have a dip in the middle, tend to be red around the circumference, + contain vesicular fluid. They can open or crust over + take a long time to heal (2-4 weeks: contagious until scabs fall off), often leaving scars. Monkeypox can also complicate + cause sepsis, bronchopneumonia, corneal infection, etc.

What do I need to know and do?

- Be aware of it
- If you have a rash, see your doctor so they can decide if it is monkeypox or another rash, and if you warrant lab testing
-Avoid direct contact with others while you are infected
- High risk groups (E.g. MSM, immune compromised, pregnant etc) can be vaccinated to limit spread and disease progression. HOWEVER, this is not available everywhere.
- Treatment is mainly supportive (treat pain, fever, etc). Antivirals like brincidofovir are not widely available and don’t have the best data, but can be tried in certain cases if warranted.

I know it may feel like it is just “one thing after another,” but this is the world we live in. Outbreaks are going to become even more common as a result of environmental exploitation, unsustainable agricultural practices, trade and migration, etc. We must remain aware and do our best to comply with outbreak containing measures informed by science.

author: countyofventura
text:
Ventura County Public Health (VCPH) officials are investigating the first documented case of Monkeypox in Ventura County, however the risk to general public is still considered low.

VCPH received a confirmed case of Monkeypox virus infection in an adult earlier yesterday morning after testing was completed at a local lab.

VCPH is conducting contact tracing with the patient to identify anyone who may be at risk due to direct close contact with the patient while infectious. People with direct close contact are being asked to watch for symptoms of illness.

If you develop a suspicious rash or were in contact with someone who has tested positive for Monkeypox, reach out to a health care provider right away for further guidance and for testing, as early recognition and testing can help prevent further transmission. Read more at news.ventura.org #monkeypox #knowthesigns #venturacounty @vchca
—
Los oficiales de Salud Pública del Condado de Ventura (VCPH, por sus siglas en inglés) están investigando el primer caso documentado de la viruela del mono en el condado de Ventura; sin embargo, el riesgo para el público en general todavía se considera bajo.

VCPH recibió un caso confirmado de la viruela del mono en un adulto ayer en la mañana, después de que se completaran las pruebas en un laboratorio local.

VCPH está realizando un rastreo de contactos con el paciente para identificar a cualquier persona que pueda estar en riesgo debido al contacto cercano con el paciente mientras estaba infeccioso. Se les pide a las personas que fueron un contacto cercano que estén atentos a los síntomas de la enfermedad.

Si desarrolla un sarpullido sospechoso o estuvo en contacto con alguien que dio positivo en la prueba de la viruela del monocomuníquese con un proveedor de atención médica de inmediato, ya que el reconocimiento y las pruebas tempranas pueden ayudar a prevenir una mayor transmisión. Obtenga más información en news.ventura.org/es.

author: morehealthglobal
text:
Monkeypox is on the rise. Here's what you should know:

1) Anyone can get #monkeypox.

2) Monkeypox spreads by close physical contact with an infectious rash, touching items such as clothing or bed sheets used by someone who has the virus, or through respiratory droplets. A pregnant woman can also spread the virus to her fetus through the placenta.

3) Monkeypox symptoms can include fever, headache, swollen lymph nodes, chills, exhaustion, muscle and backaches, and a rash. Sometimes a rash is the only sign of monkeypox. The rash can look like pimples or blisters and go through different stages over 2-4 weeks. These sores often appear on the face, palms, soles of the feet, chest, or genitals.

4) Antiviral drugs and vaccines intended to treat smallpox can also be used to prevent and treat monkeypox.

5) Individuals who are immunosuppressed and more likely to get severely ill from monkeypox can discuss with their doctor the possibility of taking antivirals such as tecovirimat (TPOXX) for further protection.
.
.
.

text:

clinic by appointment only. Due to limited vaccine supply, this clinic is limited to those who meet the CDC criteria and are 18 years or older. More dates and appointments will open as more vaccines become available.

Visit www.othena.com to book an appointment and OChealthinfo.com/monkeypox to learn more

author: khou11
text:
The Houston Health Department is allowing those with a high risk of monkeypox to get the vaccine, which includes those on HIV pre-exposure prophylaxis, also known as PrEP.

The vaccine is being offered to two different groups of people, but they are prioritizing the first group which includes those who have had contact with someone who has monkeypox and people who went to a venue where there was a high exposure to the virus through skin and sexual contact.

The second group includes those who are at high risk of getting the virus.

Click the link in our bio to read more.
#khou #khou11 #monkeypox #houstonhealth

author: correcto.id
text:
Organisasi Kesehatan Dunia (WHO) resmi menetapkan cacar monyet atau monkeypox sebagai darurat kesehatan global pada Minggu, 24 Juli 2022.

"Saya telah memutuskan bahwa wabah cacar monyet global merupakan keadaan darurat kesehatan masyarakat yang menjadi perhatian internasional," kata Direktur Jenderal WHO, Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus mengutip mengutip keterangan WHO.

Penetapan ini karena tingkat infeksi cacar monyet terus meningkat di seluruh dunia, wabah telah meningkat menjadi darurat kesehatan masyarakat.

author: nrpublichealth
text:
Let’s talk #monkeypox. This week Niagara reported its first case of monkeypox. Public Health is conducting case and contact management to identify at-risk contacts and to help prevent spread of the virus. ⁣
⁣
With the presence of monkeypox in Niagara it is important to know the symptoms, how it spreads, & how to keep yourself & others safe.⁣
⁣
Monkeypox is a rare disease not normally found in Canada & most people recover without treatment. Symptoms include fever, headache, swollen lymph nodes, exhaustion, & a rash or blisters that typically starts on the face & spreads to other parts of the body.⁣
⁣
It can spread between people, most commonly through direct contact with an infectious rash, scab, body fluids or items contaminated with the virus (like bedding or clothing). Those who have had close contact with a confirmed case, as well as individuals with multiple or anonymous sexual partners, are at high-risk for contracting the virus.⁣
⁣
During this current outbreak, infections have been primarily reported among gay, bisexual, & men who have sex with men through their close personal & sexual networks. NRPH is following provincial guidance on the administration of Imvamune vaccines to protect individuals who have had close contact with someone who has tested positive for the virus, those with high-risk contacts & those who have a higher risk of being exposed to the virus.⁣
⁣
If you have been exposed to a suspected or confirmed case of monkeypox, monitor for symptoms for 21 days. If you develop symptoms, immediately self-isolate & contact your health care provider or Public Health. ⁣
⁣
We are hosting monkeypox vaccination clinics for high-risk community members from Aug. 2 to Aug. 4, 2022. Clinics will operate by appointment only at Niagara Region Sexual Health centers.⁣
⁣
📞 Eligible individuals can book an appointment by calling 905-688-8248 ext. 7425 or 1-800-263-7248.⁣
⁣
Learn more at niagararegion.ca/monkeypox⁣

author: agenciaaids
text:
Segundo nota da pasta enviada ao UOL, dentro dos casos confirmados, 438 são procedentes do estado de São Paulo, 86 do Rio de Janeiro, 33 de Minas Gerais, 12 do Distrito Federal, 10 do Paraná, oito de Goiás, cinco na Bahia, dois do Ceará e três do Rio Grande do Sul.
•
Além desses também existem dois diagnósticos do Rio Grande do Norte, dois no Espírito Santo, três em Pernambuco, um em Mato Grosso do Sul e um em Santa Catarina.
•
O ministério não divulgou o número de casos suspeitos sob análise no país.
•
“A Pasta segue em articulação direta com os estados para monitoramento dos casos e rastreamento dos contatos dos pacientes”, disse o ministério em nota.
•
São mais de 14 mil casos da doença, diz OMS
•
O diretor-geral da OMS (Organização Mundial de Saúde), Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus afirmou ontem que já foram registrados mais de 14 mil casos de varíola dos macacos, em 71 países. Ele disse que há tendência de queda nos casos em alguns países, mas outros ainda veem uma alta, enquanto seis países reportaram seus primeiros casos na semana passada.
•
Este é um trecho da matéria original. Leia na íntegra em AgenciaAids.com.br ou na aba "NOTÍCIAS" no link da bio.
•

author: uninoticias
text:
La viruela del mono o símica (monkeypox, en inglés) es una enfermedad contagiosa que desde mayo se ha propagado en múltiples países, primero en Europa y luego en Estados Unidos, en los que históricamente no es común.

La OMS considera que el brote del virus, que ya alcanza más de 70 países, es “excepcional”.

Este sábado declaró que constituye una “emergencia pública de interés internacional”, con la esperanza de que se coordine una mayor respuesta mundial al virus.

Te mostramos los países que registran casos de viruela del mono en 2022 -en los que no suele circular el virus- y aquellos en los que es considerada endémica.

#virueladelmono #viruelasímica #monkeypox #OMS #Emergencia

👉 La información completa en el link de nuestra biografía.

author: fosnightcenter
text:
Monkeypox is spreading almost exclusively among men that have sex with men, and while that is a very unfortunate truth, we think it's important that the LGBTQ+ community is aware of the latest findings about the virus.

A recent study found that 95% of the 528 cases of Monkeypox examined were transmitted via sexual contact between men (mostly cisgender men but also one transgender man). It's likely that sexual transmission rates are much higher than initially thought, and this contradicts what we first assumed we knew about the virus: that it was easily spread through fleeting contact and everyone was equally susceptible. Just like HIV, the virus does not affect people more or less simply because of their gender or sexual identity, but sexual contact seems to be a primary driver, and it is spreading through the MSM community.

Monkeypox is a close relative of smallpox, and while it is not considered deadly, it can still be dangerous. Symptoms include fever, headaches, backache, swollen lymph nodes, and a painful rash that can cover the entire body. Symptoms typically last between 2 to 4 weeks and go away on their own, but some people require hospitalization for pain management.

If you think you have symptoms or have been in close contact with someone with monkeypox, it is important to get tested and avoid close contact with others. A two-dose vaccine is available. Contact your local health department for resources.

If you're in Buncombe County, free vaccines are available at the county health department.
Western North Carolina Community Health Services also has a supply of vaccines.
If you have questions about exposure or vaccinations, please call BCHHS at
828-250-5300 or WNCCHS at 828-285-0622.

Any other questions? Let us know how we can help in the comments, via DM, or by giving us a call at 828-724-7166. We 💙 you. We are here for you. 🏳️‍🌈

To read more about the recent study, click the link in our bio @fosnightcenter

text: Speaking with Fierce Healthcare on how US hospitals who haven’t seen cases of monkeypox yet should have preparedness and response plans in place. While majority of cases do not require hospitalizations, having good screening processes in place is still essential.

author: revistacrescer
text:
A líder técnica da Organização Mundial da Saúde (OMS) Rosamund Lewis afirmou nesta terça feira (26) que "a situação do Brasil (em relação à varíola dos macacos) é preocupante" e que os casos podem estar subnotificados por não haver testes suficientes à disposição. O país tem 813 casos confirmados da doença, segundo dados do Ministério da Saúde.

O Ministério da Saúde destacou, por meio de nota, que a doença é prioridade para a pasta, que está monitorando a situação. Ainda segundo o ministério, “testes para diagnóstico estão disponíveis para toda a população que se enquadre na definição de casos suspeitos para varíola dos macacos”.

No sábado (23), a pasta informou que articula com a OMS a aquisição da vacina contra a doença. Em nota, o Ministério da Saúde disse que as negociações estão sendo feitas de forma global com o fabricante para ampliar o acesso ao imunizante para os países com casos confirmados.

📲 Saiba mais no site (link da bio ou nos stories)

#varioladosmacacos #monkeypox #saude #oms

The vaccine is being offered to two different groups of people, but they are prioritizing the first group which includes those who have had contact with someone who has monkeypox and people who went to a venue where there was a high exposure to the virus through skin and sexual contact.

The second group includes those who are at high risk of getting the virus.

author: anclainfectologia
text:
Não há motivo para preocupação!
Emergência de saúde pública é definida pela OMS para garantir uma resposta coordenada globalmente diante de um agravo emergente.

A transmissão da monkeypox ocorre principalmente pelo contato íntimo e via respiratória, notadamente durante a relação sexual.

Deve-se manter o uso de máscaras e higiene das mãos, além de evitar contato com pessoas com lesões de pele sugestivas.

Em caso de suspeita, mantenha o isolamento e procure um serviço de saúde para melhor acompanhamento.

#AnclaInfectologia #Monkeypox #Saude

author: repjerrynadler
text:
People at high risk of contracting monkeypox are urgently seeking care at health clinics nationwide.

Today, I led over 100 of my Democratic colleagues in calling on President Biden to allocate $100 million to help clinics test for & vaccinate against this virus.

Sexual health clinics in NYC and across the country are uniquely positioned to respond to this outbreak, but they need testing kits, vaccines, additional staff, and other supplies to scale up an appropriate response.

As cases of monkeypox continue to rise, urgent action is needed to ensure that our public health system is equipped to meet the increasing demand for testing and treatment to slow the spread of this virus.

author: ilmikiwil2
text:
[ PENDPROPEDIA : WASPADA TEMUAN BARU KASUS MONKEYPOX ]

Apa itu Monkeypox?
Monkeypox adalah penyakit akibat virus yang ditularkan melalui binatang (zoonosis). Virus monkeypox merupakan anggota genus Orthopoxvirus dalam keluarga Poxviridae. Genus Orthopoxvirus juga termasuk virus variola (penyebab cacar Smallpox) dan virus vaccinia (digunakan dalam vaksin cacar Smallpox).

Mengapa dinamakan Monkeypox atau Cacar Monyet?
Monkeypox pertama kali ditemukan pada tahun 1958 di Denmark ketika ada dua kasus seperti cacar muncul pada koloni kera yang dipelihara untuk penelitian, sehingga cacar ini dinamakan 'monkeypox'.

Jika Monkeypox adalah penyakit zoonosis, hewan apa saja yang dapat menularkan?
Apakah di Indonesia pernah ditemukan kasus Monkeypox?
Terkait munculnya kasus di Inggris Raya, apakah ada risiko penularan/penyebaran ke Indonesia?
Apakah Monkeypox dapat menular?
Bagaimana Monkeypox ditularkan?

Untuk informasi lebih lanjut mengenai Kasus Monkeypox ini yuk sama-sama kita baca langsung di slide dan jangan lupa share ya!

author: robrosiello
text:
#monkeypox
.
Learn the facts…
.
The @cdcgov posted the other day images of what the lesions look like…
.
The mainstream news isn’t being clear, if informative at all…
.
Why are some cities more responsive than others? Last week I called the PA department of Health… they referred me to my County Department of Health…
.
They could only help if I’d already been exposed… no preventative shots at that time…those who’ve had it describe the pain as excruciating …
.
Chicago, NYC, San Francisco- they’re scrambling to mitigate a health disaster…see the Boston Globe article from July 19- even Provincetown saw this potential crisis in the making…
.
I’m shocked how little how many don’t know…
.
Search out facts and start asking why?
.
IT IS NOT AN STD…
.
Transmission can be as easy and can come from using the same towel or sleeping on the same sheets as someone infected…
.
Symptoms can take 2-3 weeks to manifest and then it is too late…
.
Google this mess and do 10 minutes of research… you’ll find yourself asking even more questions…
.
ANYONE can get this…
.
Not just the gays…
.
As always, thank you to @bluebaileysf for the image I reposted…
.
#pandemic #epidemic #smallpox #chickenpox #infectiousdisease #who @who #departmentofhealth #lgbt #lgbtq @h3athen

author: mynameisjro
text:
Some snaps from this past Thursday’s rally at Foley Square demanding better from the US government who has failed our communities with their delayed and negligent response to the rapidly growing #monkeypox outbreak. Some of the demands from the action include: Needing meaningful outreach to all communities including vulnerable populations, streamlined communication efforts, mass testing implementation, expedited FDA approval of TPOXX (MPX treatment), and a public plan for the US government to take action on the Bavarian Nordic stockpile (15.2 million vaccines). More can be found in the Action Network link in bio.

Shoutout to speakers @tomatos_ @zackmax123 @jawanzajames @brianrnyc @bradhoylman @ebottcher @ijenniferbarnes @ceciliagentili72 @ivypachamama @deaf_doctor_nyc @matthias @jameskrellenstein and orgs who signed on @actupny @prep4all @vocalnewyork @housingworks @treatmentactiongroup @callenlorde @risenresistnyc @middlechurch.

This is far from over. “Who keeps us safe? We keep us safe”. (Additional 📷 from @donnaaceto and @adameli)

author: clinicaamitie
text:
Nos últimos dias, um aumento rápido no número de casos de #monkeypox — ou #varíoladomacaco — vem sendo observado em diversos países do #mundo . A possibilidade de uma nova #pandemia levantou o alerta das autoridades sanitárias mundiais e é importante que todos conheçam essa #doença para pronto reconhecimento. O período de incubação de Monkeypox é geralmente de 6 a 13 dias, mas pode variar de 5 a 21 dias, período em que precisamos ficar atentos aos possíveis sinais como: calafrios, febre, dor muscular, exaustão física, dor de cabeça, dor de garganta, tosse, inchaço dos gânglios linfáticos e vermelhidão com erupções na pele que parecem espinhas ou bolhas. Presta atenção à imagens dessas lesões.
.
#alerta #dicadesaude #noticias #DrCesar #DrCesarIsaac #SP

author: bh_shac
text:
Got a rash with blisters plus aches,
a fever and swollen glands?
You could have monkeypox.

Anyone can catch it through close
physical contact, or by sharing
towels or bedsheets.

Keep everyone safe by avoiding close contact with others.
or visiting nhs.uk/monkeypox
#nhs #bhshac #Brighton #SexualHealth #monkeypox #ukhsa

author: smyrcpdx
text:
Repost from @equiinstitute -

There is a lot of misinformation concerning the global outbreak of hMPXV. Here’s what you may need to know about safety and prevention.

Please share to spread knowledge and correct information. Appropriate gender and sexual orientation data is not currently being collected so messaging around “men who have sex with men” or “AMAB” people is not inclusive of our expansive communities. All cases that have been reported to the OHA at this time are from folks who self-identified as male. The truth is that anyone, regardless of sexual orientation or gender identity, is at risk for contracting this virus without the proper precautions and awareness.

Sources: CDC, Oregon Health Authority, Multnomah County and British Journal of Medicine
.
.
.
.
.
.
#hMPXV #monkeypox #lgbtq #portland #pdx #vaccine #oregon #healthcare #oha #multnomahcounty #covid #stopthespread #cdc #lgbtqhealth

For more info, contact Douglas Hill: DougH@gmhc.org / (212) 367-1567. #safersex #monkeypox #monkeypoxnyc

author: hollywoodunlocked
text:
HU Staff: Jamal Osborne @_j.osborne
A Houston Texas man, Wesley Wallace, recently did an interview with KHOU11 to bring more awareness to monkeypox. According to the Texas Department of Health, there are now 57 cases of confirmed monkeypox in the Houston region with 183 across the state.
_______________________________________________
“It hurts to exist. Because my face isn’t touching anything. It’s not like sleeping on a pillow, ‘Oh it hurts.’ It just hurts to exist to the open air,” Wesley Wallace said.
_______________________________________________
Wallace also says he believes he got the virus during July 4th weekend when he was at the bar. “I’m going to say I was probably kissing somebody that had it and didn’t know it, just based on where my initial lesions popped up,” Wallace said.
___________________________________________________
Read more at hollywoodunlocked.com 📸: KHOU11
__________________________________________________

author: rosanagravena
text:
Confirmação do 1º caso da varíola dos macacos aqui em Jacareí.

O paciente estava internado em São José dos Campos e foi monitorado pela Vigilância Epidemiológica de Jacareí, desde quando era considerado como um caso suspeito.

Após a confirmação, a Vigilância manteve o monitoramento até o final do período recomendado pelo Ministério da Saúde, inclusive monitorando todos os familiares e pessoas que tiveram contato com o paciente. Ele teve alta e passa bem.

Fica o alerta e reforçamos a todos sobre os cuidados a serem tomados para prevenção, como o uso de máscara em ambientes fechados e a higienização das mãos.

Apesar do nome da doença, reforçamos que a transmissão não tem relação com o macaco. Ela ocorre no contato com lesões, gotículas respiratórias e materiais contaminados.

A entrevista completa vai ao ar ainda hoje na programação da Band Vale @bandvaletv, a qual agradeço pela entrevista ao repórter Lucas @lucaspetrola1 e cinegrafista Ulisses, por levar a informação até à população.
.
.
#monkeypox #varíoladosmacacos #saúde #Prevenção #VigilânciaEpidemiológica #Jacareí #RosanaGravena

author: clinica.sabbag
text:
Surto de Monkeypox não vem dos macacos!
A Clínica Sabbag auxilia nas informações adequadas:
- esse surto de varíola se originou dos roedores e na África desde os anos 1950. Essa doença se modificou sendo transmitida pessoa a pessoa e nos últimos meses se espalhou para vários países.
- não é uma doença que atinge somente o público homossexual mas tem contágio sexual predominante.
- contágio básico é pelo contato pele a pele por meio das feridinhas de uma pessoa infectada. Geralmente são casos leves e de baixa mortalidade mas de longa evolução.
- Pode haver febre quando surgem as lesões vermelhas na pele que forma bolhas pequenas e feridas com casquinhas. Nessa fase ainda é transmissível.
- talvez pessoas com psoríase e dermatite atópica tenham maior chance de contágio porque a pele está mais exposta à infecções de pele.
- a vacina da varíola que era dada até os anos 1980 pode dar uma imunidade protetiva mas não sabemos ainda.
Dr Cid Yazigi Sabbag Dermatologista e Doutor em Ciências da Saúde FMUSP. #monkeypox #varioladosmacacos #variola #varíola #clínicasabbag #drcidsabbag

text: From @rollingstone - Excerpt below and link to full article via the linktree in my bio. #monkeypox #sexworkersafety
replies:
['not.a.statistic.19
 116w
EXCERPT: On Wednesday, the pornography industry, which was lauded in the early days of the Covid-19 pandemic as a model of testing practices, released new health and safety guidelines for Monkeypox. The instructions offer advice for maintaining a safe workspace on sets and advise adult performers to get vaccinated as soon as possible.
“We’re an industry that is very familiar with testing, we’re very familiar with health and safety protocols, and we are a community that has extended contact,” says Mike Stabile, public affairs director of Free Speech Coalition, the industry’s trade association. “So I think among the members of our community, this was something that was more urgent to address than it might be perceived in the general population.” In a statement, executive director of the national PASS program (for Performer Availability Screening Services) Ian O’Brien said he organization was not aware of any infections related to adult film production, but the guidance released by PASS is meant to prevent the spread of illness. “While we are not aware of Monkeypox incidents related to adult production, we are a community that has historically taken our health, and public health, very seriously,” O’Brien said. The group also released an initial alert about the virus in May.
Long before mainstream office workers were uploading their vaccine statuses to company web portals or taking work surveys about recent Covid exposures, the adult film industry had a similar system in place to ensure the health and safety of its workers. Since 2011, PASS has partnered with testing organizations to clear people to work for two weeks at a time, based on testing for seven sexually transmitted infections, including HIV. Headlines at the start of the pandemic hailed the industry as leaders in testing to ensure workplace safety. Likewise, by June 2020, PASS had issued 30 pages of guidelines for dealing with Covid, including social distancing and PPE protocols.
Now the organization is confronting Monkeypox, a virus that spreads through body fluids, skin contact and respiratory droplets, causing flu-like symptoms and at times a painful rash.
5 likes
Reply']

author: milcod
text:
Jabbed against the #monkeypox while being a respectable gayer and doing my regular checkup/tests to make sure I'm not unintentionally being a Typhoid Mary (just a Mary, thank you very much).

If you get the opportunity to get the smallpox jab (and haven't already) then please take it. Monkeypox is VERY transmittable by touch and contact, including via surfaces, and it is not solely spread sexually despite hate-fuelled claims trying to paint it as a "gay plague" (just because many in our community take responsibility for monitoring their health and reporting cases early?) . By getting the vaccine, this is doing FAR more to halt its spread than any hysterical ramblings and claims will achieve. Also, by all reports, the pox is a horrible thing to have, so I'm glad I've taken steps to hopefully avoid that and lessen my chances, and help avoid passing it on.

#InstaGay #GaysInGlasses #WeCanDoIt

author: web_fiery_bulletin
text:
देश में मंकीपॉक्स के लगातार बढ़ते मामलों को देखते हुए सरकार सतर्क हो गई है। सरकार ने मंकीपॉक्स की वैक्सीन निर्माण के लिए 'एक्सप्रेशन ऑफ इंटरेस्य' यानि टेंडर निकाला है। इसके अलावा मंकीपॉक्स की जांच के लिए टेस्टिंग किट का भी टेंडर निकाला गया है। वैक्सीन और टेस्टिंग किट प्राइवेट-पब्लिक पार्टनरशिप मोड से बनाई जाएगी। सरकार की तरफ से जारी नोटिफिकेशन के मुताबिक 10 अगस्त तक कंपनियां ईओआई जमा कर सकती हैं।  अब तक देश में मंकीपॉक्स के चार केस मिल चुके हैं। इनमें से तीन केरल में और एक दिल्ली में है। दिल्ली में पाया गया मंकीपॉक्स का पहला मरीज एलएनजेपी अस्पताल में भर्ती है। रिपोर्ट्स के मुताबिक वह ठीक हो रहा है।

#monkeypox #virus #tender #desh #company #keral #india #wfb

author: cellco_biotec
text:
Desde que extrapolou as fronteiras da África em maio, a varíola dos macacos (#monkeypox) já se espalhou por 65 países e infectou quase 10 mil pessoas. No Brasil, já foram contabilizados perto de 900 casos, a maioria em São Paulo – mas especialistas acreditam que o vírus esteja mais espalhado, em meio às dificuldades de teste e diagnóstico.

A doença já foi identificada pela ciência desde 1958, mas agora médicos e pesquisadores tentam entender as causas da velocidade do novo surto e debatem a melhor forma para conter essa ameaça sem aumentar o estigma sobre os grupos mais vulneráveis ao vírus. Entre as estratégias, eles defendem campanhas de orientação focadas e vacinas.

Um dos principais empecilhos para dimensionar o alcance da monkeypox no Brasil e no mundo tem sido a variedade de manifestações da doença e a subnotificação. Com o período de incubação do vírus podendo variar de 5 a 21 dias, os primeiros sintomas geralmente incluem febre, dor de garganta, de cabeça e no corpo (que em alguns casos leva a uma primeira suspeita de infecção por algum vírus respiratório), além de inchaço dos gânglios. Alguns dias depois, surgem as lesões na pele, com pequenas erupções que podem se espalhar pelos dedos, mãos, braços, pescoço, costas, peito e pernas.

O surgimento dessas feridas nas regiões genital e perineal (entre o ânus e o órgão genital) tem ajudado médicos a confundir a #varíoladosmacacos com outras Infecções Sexualmente Transmissíveis (ISTs), como #sífilis e #herpes.

Os especialistas temem que a falta de testes e a demora na aquisição de imunizantes sejam entraves para conter a doença no Brasil. A Agência Nacional de Vigilância Sanitária (Anvisa) anunciou ontem (26/07) que vai dar prioridade à análise dos processos de registro de kits para diagnóstico laboratorial da varíola dos macacos (monkeypox).

Fontes: @istoedinheiro/agencia.brasil

📌Do not handle or touch the bedding, towels, or clothing of a person with monkeypox

📌Wash your hands often with soap and water or use an alcohol-based hand sanitizer

author: dramarinabucar
text:
“OMS pede aos homens gays que reduzam a quantidade de “companheiros sexuais” pela monkeypox. 98% dos casos são em homens que mantêm relações sexuais com homens”.

Quem tenha medo de falar sobre a transmissão dessa doença se preocupa mais com ser criticado pela falácia de ser “politicamente correto” que com cuidar e proteger aos pacientes mais afetados pela doença.

Nosso dever é a informação real porque nosso objetivo é a Saúde e bem estar das pessoas.

Também se contagia com o contato direto com as lesões vesiculares e por isso os cuidadores também estão em risco.

Difícil encontrar uma pessoa que veja uma vesícula no corpo de outra, principalmente se é desconhecida, e vá limpar as “bolhas” sem luvas.

#dramarinabucar
#naoaceitefalacia
#monkeypox

author: dokterfani
text:
24 Juli 2022, WHO menyatakan cacar monyet (monkeypox) sebagai Public Health Emergency of International Concern (PHEIC). (Darurat kesehatan global)
Sudah ada 16.000 kasus di 75 negara dan 5 Kasus kematian karena wabah Cacar Monyet.

Perlu diketahui, selain Monkeypox, saat ini ada 2 fokus lainnya untuk keadaan darurat kesehatan, yaitu

1. Pandemi virus corona (Covid-19) dan
2. Upaya berkelanjutan untuk memberantas polio.

author: dripsmedical
text:
On July 25th 2022, WHO Director General Dr.Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus declared Monkey Pox a Public Health Emergency of International Concern. Based on data tracking, we previously reported that the viral outbreak had reached 500 cases in over 30 countries, today there are now over 18,000 cases in at least 75 countries.

There should be no real cause for alarm as Monkeypox is usually a self-limited disease with the symptoms lasting from 2 to 4 weeks. Although, severe cases can occur. In recent times, the case fatality ratio has been around 3–6%. It is transmitted to humans through close contact with an infected person or animal, or with material contaminated with the virus. Monkeypox virus is transmitted from one person to another by close contact with lesions, body fluids, respiratory droplets and contaminated materials such as bedding. Avoiding such contact can be preventive.

The symptoms of monkeypox include fever, rash and swollen lymph nodes and may lead to a range of medical complications.

For clinical evaluation of suspicious monkey pox, we can provide Telemedicine Services with photo of skin lesions.

We will continue to follow the outbreak.

#dripsmedical
